1899
04:03:42.500 --> 04:03:54.500
It was hardly profit-making as we kept our rates low to make it affordable, and we offered tuition assistance to those who needed it.

1900
04:03:54.500 --> 04:04:05.500
And I certainly understand the need for families to find an alternative to public schools to meet the needs of their children.

1901
04:04:05.500 --> 04:04:11.500
My own two children attended the same public school where I taught.

1902
04:04:11.500 --> 04:04:17.000
My daughter was fine with it, but not so my son.

1903
04:04:17.000 --> 04:04:26.500
He was experiencing difficulties, so we sent him to a local private school until he reached middle school age.

1904
04:04:26.500 --> 04:04:30.500
It was good that we had that option.

1905
04:04:30.500 --> 04:04:39.000
