1906
04:04:39.000 --> 04:04:57.500
When I mentioned that to the good people at OLS, they explained to me that in New Hampshire, the goal always has been to write our laws in such a way that ordinary people can understand them.

1907
04:04:57.500 --> 04:05:00.500
No need for a law degree.

1908
04:05:00.500 --> 04:05:05.000
All you needed was to be able to read.

1909
04:05:05.000 --> 04:05:09.500
That goes for the state constitution too, he said.

1910
04:05:09.500 --> 04:05:14.000
I can read and I have read the constitution.

1911
04:05:14.000 --> 04:05:25.500
I have filed this bill because I believe the use of locally raised property taxes to fund scholarships to religious schools is unconstitutional.

1912
04:05:25.500 --> 04:05:31.000
It needs to be made clear in our laws as well.

1913
04:05:31.000 --> 04:05:37.000
I have provided everyone copies of several pages of our state constitution.

1914
04:05:37.000 --> 04:05:45.000
The first two pages include part one, articles one through 11 of our Bill of Rights.

1915
04:05:45.000 --> 04:05:57.500
If you look at the dates of passage, you will see that most all of them were passed in 1784, when our Constitution was established.

1916
04:05:57.500 --> 04:06:02.000
Please look at the top of the second page.

1917
04:06:02.000 --> 04:06:04.500
Article 6, Morality and Piety.

1918
04:06:04.500 --> 04:06:11.500
I have underlined the relevant sentence and I have circled the date of passage.

1919
04:06:11.500 --> 04:06:14.500
Let me read it to you.

1920
04:06:14.500 --> 04:06:24.500
But no person shall ever be compelled to pay towards the support of the schools of any sect or denomination.

1921
04:06:24.500 --> 04:06:30.000
That prohibition has been in our Constitution since its very start.

1922
04:06:30.000 --> 04:06:38.000
If you turn to page three, you will see part two, article 83 of our Constitution.

1923
04:06:38.000 --> 04:06:45.000
It too has been there since the beginning, but it has been amended twice.

1924
04:06:45.000 --> 04:06:48.000
The first time was in 1877.

1925
04:06:48.000 --> 04:06:55.000
This is two years after James Blaine from Maine first proposed his infamous amendment.

1926
04:06:55.000 --> 04:07:00.500
This is our Blaine Amendment we have heard so much about.

1927
04:07:00.500 --> 04:07:03.500
It's been called the Anti-Catholic Amendment.

1928
04:07:03.500 --> 04:07:11.000
I agree this is not nice, but nonetheless it is still part of our Constitution.

1929
04:07:11.000 --> 04:07:14.500
