1942
04:08:47.000 --> 04:09:02.000
As I read the New Hampshire Constitution, it is not allowed for the town to use our money to fund a scholarship to pay the tuition to a Christian school.

1943
04:09:02.000 --> 04:09:18.500
The separation of church and state is one of the basic tenets of American democracy, as inviolable as part one, article 2A of the New Hampshire Constitution about the right to bear arms.

